~Hello,
~
~Does anyone have any specific instructions on how to compile, install
~BIND on a Sun 3/50 running SunOS 3.5. I ftped Bind 4.7.3 from
~ucbarpa.berkeley.edu a while back. Is this the latest version? If not
~where do I get a later one. I'm new to Unix and all help is
~appreciated.
~
~Mark Miller
~
-----------

Mark,

I can't help you with your "Sun" "bind" problem, however, I received this
response about the latest version of "bind":

~From: karels%okeeffe.Berkeley.EDU@ucbvax.Berkeley.EDU (Mike Karels)
~To: gumkowsk@NADC.ARPA (D. Gumkowski)
~Subject: Re: where is the newest "bind"? 
~In-Reply-To: Your message of Fri, 18 Mar 88 11:00:04 EST.
~Date: Mon, 21 Mar 88 14:18:35 PST

~I removed the old versions of BIND on ucbarpa in preparation for installing
~the new release, to be called version 4.8, about 3 weeks ago.  The next
~morning I discovered that a change in the new version (to make it comply
~with the current RFCs) caused serious problems for older versions of BIND.
~A workaround has been installed and tested.  We are testing the installation
~procedure now, and the release will then be placed on ucbarpa.Berkeley.EDU
~for anonymous FTP from path pub/4.3/bind.4.8.tar.Z (or uncompressed,
~without the trailing .Z).  It should be there by the end of the week;
~it will be announced on the bind mailing list.
~
~	Mike
~
 Hope this is of some help.  

    Dave Gumkowski, NADC VAX analyst

